Step 1.
Open Docker Desktop to start the daemon.

Step 2. 
Clone this repository into a folder of your choice

Step 3.
Clone the .env.sample into another .env file.

Step 3.
Run the run.sh script found in devops folder, this should build 2 / 3 (depending if db is impelemtned yet) containers

Step 4.
Work away! (localhost:3000)

PS. Remember to venv and install the required components found in django/requirements.txt and put --save flag on any npm packages installed
Any changes should automatically be reflected in the containers